    "Error ratio (ErrR)Likewise, error ratio is a metric with the same intention of the error difference, but now trying to look to the comparison of both groups to try to understand how much of one group is present in the other group, or, in other words, how two distinct groups are related.The metric is defined by the following equation: For a, b ∈ A:ErrR:= F P a +F N a N b +N a F P b +F N b N b +N a (23)123This is equivalent to:ErrR:= P( Ŷ = Y, A = a) P( Ŷ = Y, A = b) (24)The ideal number is 1, which means that both false positive and negative rates for privileged and unprivileged groups are balanced.",
